5|$|Leontius was {{bishop of}} Antioch from 348 to 357. He is {{quoted in the}} Chronicon Paschale, or Paschal Chronicle, a {{universal}} chronicle of history based on the paschal cycle, as <b>an</b> <b>authority</b> <b>on</b> the martyrdom of Babylas. The quotation describes Philip seeking penitence from Babylas for the sin of murdering his predecessor.|$|E
